@Node Einleitung "Introduction"

@{B} I N T R O D U C T I O N @{UB}
__________________________________________________________________________
@{FG SHINE}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{FG TEXT}


AHI is a kind of Retargetable Audio System, written by Martin Blom.
It supports several sound boards, and now also the MacroSystem's
MaestroPro digital sound board.

This wasn't a piece of cake to do, since the MaestroPro is somewhat
special. For example, AHI isn't much into changing sampling rate
lists, but as you know, the sampling rate of the board depends on
the incoming signal's rate.

Thus, the usage of the AHI driver is somewhat different (see the
chapter about it's @{" usage " link Usage} ).


                                                Richard Körber

@EndNode
@Node Required "Requirements"

@{B} R E Q U I R E M E N T S @{UB}
__________________________________________________________________________
@{FG SHINE}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{FG TEXT}


MaestixAHI requires:

   · 68020 or higher. A 68000 version is available from the
     @{" Author " link Adresse} upon request. You do not need a FPU.

   · The maestix.library V40.10 or higher (V40.00 won't do!)

   · AHI V4 (it might also run with V2, but I tested it on V4).

   · A MaestroPro sound board (of course).
     The old Maestro isn't supported, and will never be!

@EndNode
